http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Journalism IV is designed to provide students in media leadership the opportunity to facilitate the production process. Students in Journalism IV will use their advanced journalistic knowledge and leadership skills to facilitate all aspects of media production and to ensure that journalistic guidelines for writing and design, which include objectivity, responsibility, and credibility, are followed. Writing, technology, and visual and electronic media are used as tools for learning as students lead, create, evaluate, and produce.
Law and Ethics
Students will evaluate legal and ethical issues.
Create staff policies that address legal and ethical issues for media
Evaluate journalistic work according to ethical responsibilities
History
Students will develop knowledge of the history and role of journalism in society.
Evaluate current events in journalism in a democratic society
Integrate concepts from current events in contemporary journalism to established media
Evaluate photography in contemporary journalism

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: (e.g., emotional connection, how photo enhances text, reader response, storytelling quality of the photo)

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Management and Organization
Students will demonstrate a working knowledge of staff management and organization.
Create staff organizational and time management strategies necessary to meet production schedules
Create a staff plan for financing the media production
Create a staff plan to maximize the circulation of media
Design and Production
Students will create designs for media.
Create a plan to use available technology for media production
Create advanced designs for media production
Evaluate and edit designs according to established design principles and trends

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: (e.g., current trends, design principles, layout style)

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Writing
Students will create various pieces of journalistically sound writing.
Evaluate original interview questions using advanced research skills in various forms of writing
Compose various forms of advanced journalistically sound writing suitable for publication
Critique journalistically sound writing suitable for a publication
Evaluate various forms of writing suitable for a journalistically sound publication using advanced style

Edit various forms of writing suitable for a journalistically sound publication:
  • self edit
  • peer edit
Photography
Students will demonstrate a working knowledge of photographic principles.
Edit visual pieces for photographic principles in media production
Integrate photographic pieces to incorporate in media production
